      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JESSICAS STORY (4) added to her consistent form at her latest appearance when she used the sprint lane to get home at Kilmore, scoring by 4 metres. Draws a few spots wider but with even luck she is going well enough to take out a race like this. ALABAMA MAY (3) was beaten just a nose here two back then was runner-up again at her latest appearance at Maryborough, beaten 2.6 metres. Came from the back row in both of those outings so should enjoy this favourable draw and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance. AFRICAN GALA (12) cops a tricky draw but enjoys a big class drop from Listed level and is race fit now. WHATS THE TEA (13) may need luck from this barrier but is racing well, producing two solid efforts since a Kilmore win.",
